vehicles_data.description: Compilation of Vehicles for Star Wars SAGA Edition. This batch includes initial Core Rulebook entries.

vehicle_list.name: AAT-1 (Armored Assault Tank)
vehicle_list.full_text_description: The AAT-1 is a heavily armored repulsorlift tank used by the Trade Federation and later the Confederacy of Independent Systems. It is designed for front-line assaults to soften up enemy defenses before deploying battle droids. It is noted for its ion vulnerability.

special_qualities_systems.name: Ion Vulnerability
special_qualities_systems.description: Due to a design flaw, the AAT takes double damage from ion weapons.

vehicle_list.name: AT-AT (All-Terrain Armored Transport)
vehicle_list.full_text_description: The 22.5-meter-tall All Terrain Armored Transport (AT-AT) is an imposing, four-legged behemoth that shakes the ground as it plods toward enemy fortifications. Used by the Empire to overwhelm Rebel forces on Hoth.

special_qualities_systems.name: All-Terrain
special_qualities_systems.description: Can traverse difficult terrain without penalty.

special_qualities_systems.name: Troop Transport
special_qualities_systems.description: Designed to carry troops into battle.

vehicle_list.name: AT-ST (All-Terrain Scout Transport)
vehicle_list.full_text_description: The 8.6-meter-tall All-Terrain Scout Transport (AT-ST) is a nimble, two-legged mobile weapons platform that rapidly moves across battlefields and through cramped urban environments, providing reconnaissance and quick-response fire support for ground troops.

vehicle_list.name: X-34 Landspeeder
vehicle_list.full_text_description: One of the most popular models of civilian speeders is the SoroSuub X-series, which can attain a maximum altitude of 1.5 meters. It is a durable two-person craft that features holographic displays, computer-assisted navigation, and counterbalances for a stable ride over rough terrain. Luke Skywalker used an X-34 landspeeder on Tatooine.

special_qualities_systems.name: Open Cockpit
special_qualities_systems.description: Crew has cover (+5 to Reflex Defense).

vehicle_list.name: 74-Z Speeder Bike
vehicle_list.full_text_description: The 74-Z is a basic speeder bike designed for military scouting and urban patrol missions. It consists of a powerful repulsorlift engine with two small thrust engines, a long forward control vane, and a small blaster cannon in a rotating forward mount. It is designed for a single pilot but has room for a passenger as well—both straddling the engine block of the vehicle.
